article.headline: Drake 75, S. Dakota St. 65
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa -- Brent Heemskerk scored 12 points and pulled down 10 rebounds to lead Drake to a 75-65 win over South Dakota State in the second round of the Cancun Challenge on Sunday. Heemskerk was 6-of-11 from the field and grabbed six offensive rebounds for Drake (2-1). Jonathan Cox led the Bulldogs in scoring with 15 points, and five Drake players scored in double digits. Garrett Callahan led all scorers with 21 points, including going 4-for-8 from 3-point range, but the Jackrabbits (1-3) couldn't overcome a six-minute scoreless drought in the first half. Drake trailed 4-2 early, but rolled off a 10-0 run while South Dakota State turned the ball over five times and missed four consecutive shots. Drake took its biggest lead on a Cox layup with 7:03 left to go up 61-46. The Jackrabbits kept pace with the Bulldogs in the second half, but couldn't overcome the early deficit.
